CORPORATE POLICY — PLANT ASSET MANAGEMENT & ROLE ACCESS CONTROL
Policy Ref: POL-001 | Version: v5.0 | Approved By: Executive Board

1. PURPOSE & APPLICABILITY
Establishes clear operational governance, role permissions, and asset management responsibilities across all industrial plants.

2. ROLE RESPONSIBILITIES MATRIX
- Plant Manager: Executive oversight of plant KPIs, approval of spare part purchase orders, verification of completed high-priority work orders.
- Maintenance Engineer: On-ground work order execution, preventive maintenance logging, spare part stock checks, LOTO compliance.
- Reliability Engineer: Conducting Root Cause Analysis (RCA), predictive maintenance modeling, RUL evaluation, vibration telemetry analysis.
- Quality Engineer: Managing non-conformance reports (NCRs), scheduling and executing statutory compliance audits, ISO 9001 quality framework maintenance.
- Safety Officer: HSE policy enforcement, safety inspection tracking, receiving completion alerts, managing machine operating licenses and insurance coverage.
- Document Controller: Ingestion and metadata tagging of technical manuals, engineering drawings, SOPs, and compliance records in the AI Document Repository.